</Column>
<Row background="#191c22" padding="0,10%">
    <Column width="1/2" align="left" justify="center" padding="5%">
        <Text color='#d7ffc5' uppercase='true' spacing='0.3em' font='mono' margin='15px,0'>_ARCHITECTURE_OVERVIEW</Text>
        <Text type='h3' color='#cccccc' font='extrabold' spacing='min' uppercase='true' margin='0,20px,0,0'>THE HEXAGONAL CORE</Text>
        <Text type='p' color='#cccccc' margin='0,15px,0,0'>Infrastructure changes. Business logic doesn't. OmniPort isolates your src/application from the volatile world of APIs and databases. </Text>
        <Container background="#32353c" color="#d7ffc5" width="100%" padding="20px" border="0,0,2px,0">
            <Text type='h6' font='bold' spacing='min' uppercase='true'>ZERO LOGIC DUPLICATION</Text>
            <Text type='p' color='#cccccc'>Write your validation logic once. Serve it to a React frontend, a CLI tool, and an IoT adapter simultaneously without changing a single line of domain code.</Text>
        </Container>
    </Column>
    <Container width="1/2">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 1000 1000" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <defs>
                <style type="text/css">
                    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Segoe+UI:wght@400;700&amp;display=swap');
                    text { font-family: 'Segoe UI', sans-serif; fill: white; }
                    .section-line { stroke: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); stroke-width: 1; fill: none; }
                    .infra-arc { fill: none; stroke-width: 80; opacity: 0.15; }
